ge was simple: by renouncing the individual will, anyone can become a “son of God” and thereby usher in a millennialist heaven on earth. Clark Davis’s masterful biography shows how Very came to embody both the full radicalism of Emersonian ideals and the trap of isolation and emptiness that lay in wait for those who sought complete transcendence. God’s Scrivener tells the story of Very’s life, work, and influence in depth, recovering the startling story of a forgotten American prophet, a “brave saint” whose life and work are central to the development of poetry and spirituality in America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAmerican literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism2DLC. 0aAmerican literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMysticszMassachusettsvBiography2DLC. 0aMysticszMassachusettsvBiography. 0aPoets, Americany19th centuryvBiography2DLC. 0aPoets, Americany19th centuryvBiography. 0aReligion and literaturezUnited States2DLC. 0aReligion and literaturezUnited States. 0aTranscendentalism (New England)2DLC. 0aTranscendentalism (New England). 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh  aJones Very, transcendentalist, sonnets, individualism, critical biography, Ralph Waldo Emerson.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z978311131826408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226828695423Coveruhttps://w